# Wireshark Network Traffic Investigation

## Goal

Learn how network traffic is generated, captured, and analyzed using Wireshark by investigating 
the communication that occurs when visiting common websites.

## Skills Practiced

- Wireshark
- Packet Capture
- DNS Analysis
- TCP/IP
- TLS/HTTPS
- HTTP
- IPv6
- Packet Filtering

## What I Learned

- How DNS queries resolve domain names to IPv6 addresses using AAAA records
- The difference between well-known ports and ephemeral ports
- How TCP and TLS work together to establish secure web connections
- Why Certificate Revocation Lists (CRLs) may be delivered over HTTP
- How to reconstruct a basic timeline of network activity using packet captures

## Project Files

- 3-Wireshark.pdf

## Reflection
I was amazed to see how much traffic was generated just from opening three websites. The back and forth is done so quickly, 
its incredible. I was also interested to see that I had any HTTP traffic, but it showed me something new about CRLs. 
Live and learn!


## More to Explore
- Look into what part of the traffic flow used UDP.
- See what sending an email or instant message looks like.
